caption: I call this superb place every couple of days because I like the good mood that is part of this restaurant. The staff is extraordianrillyremarkably attentive and qualified. The service is very rapid. Also, the food you get is outstanding. I visited many times and I was always pleased. The expense is modest. I highly suggest this place to my friends and family.

Great place for Indian food! I've had their chicken/lamb/beef curries, appetizer sampler with 5 different kinds of pakoras and samosas, kheer, lassi, and gulab jamun and everything was delicious. Highly recommend

Words cant explain the euphoria that has come over me from enjoying this Indian experience. My co-worker and I wanted to celebrate Birthday/Diwali together. So we ordered some classics. The delivery was timely, food packaged great, gravy rice ratio perfect, and  flavorful.  Chicken tikka masala/Butter Chicken/kolize poori wali were awesome.
Extraordinary atmosphere and very affable service. The meals were fresh and enchanting. Will clearly recommend this restaurant to friends and family. Reasonable rates and large meals. Great job.
My favorite Indian restaurant in the neighborhood. Food is always fresh, tasty and with generous portions.  The prices are very reasonable and their mulligatany soup is the best I’ve had in the city!
We have been ordering from Polash for 10 yrs now. The food is consistent, tasty and very comforting. Definitely worth a try!
Basic place but reliably good. Recommended.

We get takeout here regularly. My daughter loves the fiery hot vegetable vindaloo. I normally like food spicy, but can only manage a bite of her vindaloo! Good flavor and many vegetarian choices compared to other Indian restaurants in the area.

Absolutely delicious! Polash is our favorite Indian restaurant anywhere!!! I wish they would open a 2nd in The Bronx. My family and I have been dining there for over 13 years. Our favorite dish is the Mixed Malai. But the Tandoori chicken is a close second. No visit is complete without some delicious samosas, banana fritters, and two orders of naan (garlic and butter). I would recommend this restaurant to everyone!!!!

The chutneys and daal and mango lassi were watery, but everything was flavorful, and the samosas were good. We ordered the (spicy) vindaloo and chicken saag and mutter paneer. I requested no straw but they still gave me a plastic straw, at least they didn't give us any plastic utensils.
Real proper taste. Good people working there, quick delivery and consistent.

We arrived at this place for a meeting. This restaurant was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was very successful. The crew were very polite and we had a fantastic feeling. The meal was fresh and delicious. We enjoyed every moment and we will visit this place again. We recommend this place to all.

I ordered two appetizers and Chicken Tikka Masala. For the appetizers, I had samosas and garlic naan. The appetizers were phenomenal. The garlic naan  was warm and sumptuous. The samosas were warm and crunchy. The chicken was not tasty at all, in fact it tasted rubbery.
(Translated by Google) This Indian dish is good and looks bad, but it doesn't have holes in it, it is cheap and delicious.  (Original) 这家印度菜不错，外观看上去不行，但里面别有洞天，物美价廉味道好。
Delicious Indian food! Vegan and vegetarian options available.
Super delayed delivery, not worth the two hours of wait at all. -ve stars

First time here and strangely empty.  The food was really good, the water service was excellent.  I ordered Lamb Spinach, and was asked how spicy: I asked for spicy, and I was amazed that it was actually spicy.  Highly recommend it looking for good Indian food in this area.

Service was really good. Our waiter was nice and constantly taking care of us.  The buffet option is pretty great too. Awesome food for a low cost to our pockets. Definitely get the beef when you go for lunch, you wont regret it!
Very friendly staff and food was delicious!
Love the food but one of the mango ice cream was half full.
Good food but on the mild side. If you like spice, ask for it!

We met with friends at this spot for dinner. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was a winning. The staff welcomed us with a smile and we had a fantastic feeling. The meal was yummy. We had a great time and we shall absolutely come back again. Recommended.
I only do pickup and food is always hot and tasty. Lots of lunch specials available for $6.95, lots of vegan options too.  $10 minimum for card payments.
Food excellent, hospitality excellent, atmosphere calm, and clean. A bit pricey but the food was so good.
Absolutely the best Indian food I’ve had in this city!
Polash is a good place to eat. They have a good size menue and the food is tasty and filling. They also have at around 12 an all you can eat lunch special with a small but great selection of food.
Absolutely terrible butter chicken. Worst Indian restaurant I've ordered food from. They should be ashamed of serving food so bad, and making Indian food look bad in the process.

$20 gets you 4 small (amazingly delicious) appetizers, a main dish, soup, side, vegetable, desert and tea (I might be missing something). This place, hands down, has the best bang for your buck, while also manages to be some exquisite Indian food. If I could give Polash 10 stars, I would. Try their saag paneer.
I love the breads here. Tried the vindaloo last time, it was very good.
Great flavor
Great service but terrible food. I have never eaten food this bad!
Good food will go again
Quiet inside here but don't let that fool you. Place was clean, service was good and the food was on point.  We'll be back for sure.
Great time

I’m honestly planning my next visit here this week ! The food was amazing!! The tables decorated nicely, I love the way the dishes are served ! I had the chicken curry it was awesome! I recommend this restaurant and can’t wait to return!🔥

This is a really more than decent place, it's so wonderful to come to since the workers there are very respectful;  accommodating and generous. That's what I like about going there first, then of course the food is delicious..cooked just the right way. So I had to give it 5 stars!!
So so ....
Delicius plates. And great customer service
The Indian food is excellent.  The Service is great. Been going there for years. Love their bread Rooty.
Great food and hospitality.

Big No If you are a vegetarian....Very bad experience as a vegetarian.. there was a big piece of meat mixed in vegetarian curry, when shown there are no regrets seen on their face.. they just wanted to remove the big piece n bring the curry back..definitely not for vegetarians..
Great food!!!
Best Place To Eat For Your Money Great People And Service.
Great affordable fresh delicious and fast delivery. We’ve been ordering the same thing for 8 years.
Really great place and the service was on point. Will be returning.
Excellent food, great prices, accommodating staff.
Elegant.
Great food at a great price.

(Translated by Google) Good quality not all dishes are spicy with strong scent, clean, recommended.  (Original) Buona la qualità non su tutti i piatti molti sono speziati con profumo forte , locale pulito , consigliato.
Great place polash

The fritters and other fried item they had at the lunch buffet were good. Everything else was pretty basic. I ordered a side of garlic naan bread, there was no salt. An all you can eat buffet for the price was sufficient, nothing to write home about.

Worst service & quality of food is also insane... buffet was empty even we arrived 45mins before buffet ending time, we ordered dinner meat meal they gv very less portion and smelly food, rice was old cooked and hard also careful while asking for anything as they added 3$ if u ask for sauce or onions, worst experience
The food was good now its not to good
Always love it!!
We come for the buffet and it’s amazing for how cheap it is.
I love Indian food.  The lunch buffet is really good and you get full so quick..  😊

My favorite food is Chicken tikka Masallah. The owner runs this restaurant himself. The staff is super friendly and professional. The garlic naan is far better than any garlic naan I had. The tandoori chicken is delicious. It’s cooked to perfection. Other restaurants make their chicken too hard or too soft. This restaurant always makes sure to cook things to perfection and serve it elegantly. I often come here for lunch. The lunch buffet is very affordable. If you want to ever experience one of the best Indian cuisine restaurant, then I highly recommend this place. Also, this restaurant does delivery. Their deliveries are actually super fast. This is my go to Indian cuisine I order from seamless.

Ordered dinner last night, spent 38 dollars plus tips, only received chicken rice bread, no vegetables no dessert no tea no coffee at 17.95 a plate ordered 2plates , food was tasty but I'm disappointed in the service, like we're is the rest of my dinner 🤔😲😤

Staff/Decor/Service (CHEF OWNED)  This place catered my brothers party. Amazing staff. Professional. Beautiful Decor  Food  Love the chicken tikka masalla. Garlic nan also. Not everyone knows how to cook lamb. But the owner (CHEF) makes the best lamb dishes here. He literally has like 10 different lamb dishes.  Delivery  This place has like over 2400+ Reviews on Seamless. Love the fast delivery. This is my go to place whenever I am in the mood for Indian Cuisine.  I seriously could not stand the sight of some negative reviews for this restaurant. I honestly love the food from here. I wish I could give 10/10. Keep up the good Work Polash. One of the best Chef-Owned Restaurant that serves Amazing Indian Food.

Laid back place place in a nice spacious room with well spread tables and chairs and a quiet atmosphere. The service is attentive and nice but not rushed so it's easy to sit back and enjoy the buffet at your own pace.  I've only tried the buffet and the food is freshly cooked and tasty with regular buffet refills. The Banana fritters stand out and keep coming. Beer and Wine is a nice bonus.
I'd rate five but I just said down. Came for dinner. Will come back for lunch buffet. Got a Indian restaurant back home and this definitely satisfies the hankering I had for indian cuisine.

Food never came, worst delivery service ever!!!ordered my food 2 hours ago, I call the restaurant and the guy tries to tell me they had already delivered to my apartment when clearly  they didn’t, never heard my buzzer ring, never even got a phone call. The owner of the restaurant then tries to argue with me saying it’s my fault and to take it up with seamless, very rude and very unprofessional. First time I ordered from this place and the last!!!

Decent service and decent food. Indian food is my favorite cuisine and I have enjoyed it all over the world, but indeed this was some of the worst Indian I have ever had. However, I will still give it 3 stars because it tasted good, I'm just a snob I guess. The saag Panner was tasty and the tandoori chicken was pretty good.  The butter chicken and nav ratan korma were not thick curries, they seem to have been out through a blender as if preparing food for a baby. Garlic naan was good and we tried the almond naan which turned out to be fantastic! Even when Indian food is sub par it still tastes good. Each dish is between 9-11 dollars and it comes with rice, which is good because most restaurants charge separately for rice.
This place makes you feel welcome and at home. Excellent food and Fine service. I reccomend this restaurant to everyone.
Great good. Reasonably priced.  Great service at restaurant.
Great food ,good prices....my daughter said it was the best Indian food she's ever had
The most tasty food.   Love the food.
One of my favorite Indian spots. Food is great. They just need to improve the air conditioning.
Nice ppl. Very accommodating. I'm vegan... they made sure to check and double check for me to website that everything was vegan. Great food as service!
Excelent service, good food.

My husband and I have been going there for over 10 years now... We 1st went on our 8th anniversary... It's very cozy and romantic atmosphere... Especially at night... They're open till 11:oo pm...and have the best Indian dishes around town...

Another great Indian spot I go to in the neighborhood have been coming here for the past 3 years at least 2 times every week for there all you can eat lunch buffet. The food is always fresh and the staff is great .. have beer and wine selection which is not bad either . There tandoori chicken is amazing . If you are looking for lunch buffet or great Indian dinner this is a place I suggest . And for the price it's amazing.
Best Indian food around.
Excellent food!
The most delicious of foods. The quality of the beef and lamb curry are beyond description. The quality of service is also excellent.
Food is very good, well cooked and seasoned! I enjoy their buffet options very much. Food is affordable. Staff are extremely kind and accommodating.
A treasure of Indian delights hidden in east Harlem
Good food great service good atmosphere
My husband and I go to the Polash Indian restaurant on our every  year  anniversary.  It's a  very good  , cozy  ,romantic place to eat...
Not good
Outstanding in every sense of the word!!

Food was very good, the same however cannot be said about their business practices. Ordered: Lamb Tika Masala online menu pricing-10.95 Actual charge- 11.95 Naan online menu pricing- 2.00 Actual charge- 2.50 Vegetable Samosa online menu pricing- 2.50 Actual charge- 3.95
Nice place, good service, delicious food. And the price for all you can eat is acceptable :)
Food very fresh and testy. Food price $$ is good. Employee are very friendly. I liked. O yeah everyone come
The food was made just right. Not greasy or spicy like the surrounding restaurant that serves Indian food
Good food, servings are moderate and service is just ok
I eat butter chicken here and there from this for place and is amazing you gotta try it and And thundery chickens with butter or garlic naan Is banging.TRUST ME

They have really good food there . They are so unique when it comes to their food that's what I love about them . I go there almost every week . Everyone there is very nice and the restaurant it's so clean and friendly . Feels like a high end restaurant and the food prices are good not too expensive thank God. You need to everything and the butter chicken is so so so good and everything else there . GO YOU WON'T REGRET IT 😁😁😁
Wish it was a bit spicier.
Amazing food. Very authentic. One of the best Indian food I've had in the US.

First thing first. I am indian and have been eating indian food all my life. ** Butter Chicken Alert** If you know what butter chicken is then PLEASE DO NOT ORDER FROM HERE. You will be utterly surprised and DISGUSTED. It's down right nasty and an insult to Butter Chicken. Like another reviewer, we threw ours out also but after calling the restaurant thinking that there must be a mistake in our order. The first person claimed "well that's how we make it". So i asked for a manager and i have NEVER spoken to anyone so rude. I asked if a mistake had been made and he replied that , "no, this is how we make it and have made it for years", he also stated that i "should have read the description".  Wait what, why would i need to read the description on Butter Chicken. And all we ordered was Butter Chicken and Nans. He then had the audacity to state that "you must have wanted to order mughlai chicken." No FOOL, i wanted and ordered butter chicken, not what looked like chicken swimming in puke.  *** Listen, all you have to do is order it and see for yourself. But please compare it first to authentic indian butter chicken, not to This is how "we" make it butter chicken. ***
I love the food, always fresh and tasty

The only thing better than the excellent service is the phenomenal food. I've eaten here before and the food was fine. But recently they must have made some changes because the food has been outstanding.

Love this restaurant, I come here with my friend everytime I visit NY-the food is delicious, I really love the saag paneer and the mango lassi! Also the service is great, the people there are so friendly and are generous with food on the house.
Great food and great service.
Great food!!!!!
Very nice and friendly place. Delicious Bangladeshi, Indian, and Pakistani food. Service is awesome.
Great Indian food!
I love this resturant my family is the people who work there thank you all for writing all these nice comments about our family resturant.

Ordered two entrees rice and mulagatany soup with the appetizer sample (pakora, samosa, etc..) I did not realize the food came with basmati rice for each entree and lentil soup!! Needless to say we got way more food then we thought we would which was a happy surprise because now we have leftovers for lunch! Our meal came to 40 with tip and for two people and for two meals that's a great deal!! Also they delivered, and the estimated time was 45-60min but they were here in 30min! Bonus 🙌 the food was hot and delicious, generous portions, very tasty, and I highly recommend the appetizer sampler because it's a great value for trying out a few items, and the mulagatany soup is sooooooooo good! Best red lentil soup I've ever had in my life. Hands down. We also had the mushroom and spinach entree with tomatoes and I highly recommend that too, it was very good 👌 huge selection of vegetarian options, good prices, fast delivery and tasty food! 5⭐️
Alhamdulliah The food here is great
This is a great place to eat. The food is great and authentic. Not a romantic place but great place to socialize or just a moment to enjoy your food alone.

A great place locally for Indian food. The prices are great and so is flavor. They also deliver via seamless  and always take less time to arrive than stated. The delivery guys are also very nice. They always add dal to the delivery as well. Enjoy the Rasmalai as well!

This is one of the best places in NYC where you can grab traditional Indian (especially Bengali) food that is a treat for the taste buds that crave the delectable Indian curries. The manager, Hussain is extremely hospitable and so are the other staff members. The prices are very reasonable too as compared to other Indian restaurants in NYC!
Ordered takeout delivery time was within an hour. The flavor of the food was one of the worst I have ever had. Food taste better at Red Chili Indian restaurant 116th and Lenox avenue.

Food is great, though every time I've gone to the buffet I arrive with a little over an hour to enjoy it, and they seem to not refill any of the available food.  If you go earlier...it's perfectly great. So that's what I'll do.
Literally the best Indian food I've ever had.

Cozy, good service..though it can take forever for them to serve. Food was okay. Not too good. It was like everything was dipped in oil. And what kicked me off was at the end of the day when I got my takeout and first thing I saw after opening the box was a strain of hair.

I have been to Indian restaurants all over the world, and give this one very high ratings.  For NYC the prices are amazingly reasonable, such as two samosas for $2.50 and dinner entrees with ample portions for under $10 (check menu to verify prices).  If you ask for "spicy," be warned that they take you seriously, so if you're not used to "hot," maybe try mild or medium first.  The flavors are solidly good with the right level of complexity.  The aloo paratha was well stuffed with potatoes.  The service is good, and they even gave me a little bowl of dal "on the house."  Worth traveling to get there, especially for a family dinner in a relaxing atmosphere.
Good food the service is good. We were the only table in the restaurant.
What a great place! Food is delicious and the service is great. I love how they serve the food in nice dishes. Highly recommended!
Quaint sit-down restaurant with a broad and delicious range of Indian food. Lots of variety and vegetarian.
The service was great. Very friendly and great authentic Indian food! Would recommend.

I always go for the Sunday afternoon service. Grest service. A treasure in a neighborhood full of Spanish restaurants. Great taste, great price. Highly recommend this place. They make an effort to know you and remember your order. Definitely not a wasted visit.
Fresh food and nice atmosphere
So glad to find outstanding indian in Harlem. Friendly staff and ample seating in a great local restaurant. We'll be back many times without a doubt.  Hands down, my favorite restaurant in NYC.

I came here for a quite dinner with my boyfriend and was not disappointed. The interior is big and spacious, and there's a full bar. The waitstaff are very friendly and attentive, I swear my water glass never had a chance to be empty! The food is flavorful, delicious, and filling; if you order an appetizer and an entree, you will leave here totally stuffed! I especially liked that when I asked for my dish to be on the spicy side, it was actually SPICY! Definitely my go-to place for Indian in the area.

Came here with a group of 8.  Restaurant is large enough to accommodate large groups.  Ambiance and decoration is so so.  Service was excellent.  Waiters were friendly.  We ordered regular nan, goat rogon josh, chicken kadai, lamb curry, chicken curry, somosa, shammi kabab, and other things that I forgot.  Reason for the 4 stars was the goat rogon josh.  Even though the meat was on a bone, the meat was tender and extremely flavorful.  I expect Indian cuisine to have tons of bold flavors and they definitely delivered.  Caution, one of us ordered a dish to be very spicy and it was VERY spicy.  I eat spicy foods a lot and this was really spicy.  The mild and regular/normal spicyness is good enough for majority of the people.  The lamb curry was just okay because it was chewy.  The shammi kabab was surprisingly very good.  It didn't look appetizing but it was delicious.  You got the meat flavor and the coriander wasn't overpowering.  I don't think they make their own nan, but at least it was hot when it arrived.  It wasn't sitting around forever.  The sauces were tasteful and my Indian friends agreed.  I would recommend this place and I would come back and dine here again.

Went for dinner with my wife and daughter and enjoyed our meal, thoroughly. When we got there a gentleman was just finishing his meal  and then we were the only people in the restaurant, which was strange, but the phone didn't stop ringing so it appeared to us that most of their customers are delivery orders... which I have read from reviews before going, a lot of people order by phone.  To the meal: The Mulligatawny soup was superb, Tomato/Lemony - very tasty, I loved it! We also had the veggie samosa's (great) & chicken liver as an app, which was pretty good - it came with delicious poori and I added some condiments; Tomato & Lime Chutney - a perfect compliment (which I almost finished on the papdam that greeted us at our table) . For our entree's we had Chicken Tikka Masala, it was pretty good... the sauce tasted a bit like tomato sauce, but it wasn't that bad....not the worst, not the best. We also ordered the Lamb Roganjosh - this was incredible! Very tender lamb, juicy and such a delicious sauce. We ordered Garlic Naan with dinner and it also was delicious.  Overall the food was very good, the prices were great and I would definitely go back for more.
